value.value: An endothelial cell that is part of the peritubular capillary of the kidney. This cell is highly fenestrated and plays a vital role in the kidney's filtration process, enabling the exchange of materials between the blood and the renal tubules.
Peritubular capillary endothelial cells feature fenestrations measuring 60-70 nm in diameter, each traversed by a thin diaphragm.
A cell that is part of a vasa recta.

An endothelial cell that lines the interior surface of the afferent arteriole and maintains vascular tone. This cell responds to changing ion concentrations and blood pressure by releasing vasoactive substances, in order to regulate blood flow into the glomeruli, which is essential for glomerular filtration.
Any endothelial cell that is part of some renal efferent arteriole.

label.value: kidney loop of Henle thick ascending limb epithelial cell

value.value: An epithelial cell that is part of some loop of Henle thick ascending limb. It is known in some mammalian species that this cell may express the Na+-K+-2Cl− cotransporter (NKCC2) apically.

label.value: kidney loop of Henle thin ascending limb epithelial cell

definition.value: An epithelial cell that is part of some loop of Henle thin ascending limb.

label.value: kidney loop of Henle medullary thick ascending limb epithelial cell

definition.value: An epithelial cell that is part of some loop of Henle thick ascending limb segment located in the renal medulla.

label.value: kidney loop of Henle cortical thick ascending limb epithelial cell

definition.value: An epithelial cell that is part of some loop of Henle thick ascending limb segment located in the renal cortex.

label.value: kidney loop of Henle thin descending limb epithelial cell

definition.value: An epithelial cell that is part of some loop of Henle thin descending limb.
A cell that is part of some vasa recta ascending limb.

value.value: It is known in some mammalian species that this cell may express PV-1, a component of the fenestral diaphragm.

definition.value: A cell that is part of a collecting duct of renal tubule.
A cell that is part of some vasa recta descending limb.

value.value: It is known in some mammalian species that this cell may express the urea transporter B.

definition.value: A pericyte cell located in the kidney interstitium.

value.value: Any cell that is part of some urinary bladder.
Any cell that is part of some urethra.
A urothelial cell that is part of the urothelium of the urinary bladder.
Any renal principal cell that is part of some collecting duct of renal tubule.
Any renal intercalated cell that is part of some collecting duct of renal tubule.
An epithelial cell of the exocrine pancreas.
An inhibitory, GABAergic projection neuron in the striatum that integrates glutamatergic signals arising from the cerebral cortex and thalamus.
The neurons that utilize glycine as a neurotransmitter.
Any endothelial cell of vascular tree that is part of some lung.
Any endothelial cell of vascular tree that is part of some pulmonary artery.
Squamous cell of tonsil epithelium.
Glial cell of cerebral cortex.
A glial cell that is part of the hippocampus.
Glandular cell of colon epithelium. Example: Goblet cells; enterocytes or absorptive cells; enteroendocrine and M cells.
Glandular cell of oviduct epithelium. Example: peg cells, ciliated cells.
A glandular cell found in the epithelium of the small intestine. Example: Enterocytes, Goblet cells, enteroendocrine cells; Paneth cells; M cells; Somatostatin-secreting Cells (D-cells) .
Glandular cell of exocrine pancreas epithelium. Example: pancreatic acinar cell, glandular cells in pancreatic canaliculi, glandular cells in pancreatic ducts.
Circulating macrophages and tissue macrophages (alveolar macrophages) of lung.
Chondrocyte forming the hyaline cartilage found in joints.

Hematopoietic cells resident in the bone marrow. Include: hematopoietic stem cells (lymphoid stem cells and myeloid stem cells) and the precursor cells for thrombocytes, erythrocytes, basophils, neutrophils, eosinophils, monocytes and lymphocytes.
Neuron of the cerebellum.
Any melanocyte that is part of a epidermis.

definition.value: These cells are found primarily, but not exclusively, in primates including humans

value.value: Any macroglial cell that is part of a brain.
Any blood vessel endothelial cell that is part of a microvascular endothelium.
Any lung endothelial cell that is part of a microvascular endothelium.
Any native cell that is part of a sebaceous gland.
Any glutamatergic neuron that is part of a cerebellum.
Any neuron that is part of a central nervous system.
A neuron that is part of a peripheral nervous system.
Any microvascular endothelial cell that is part of a urinary bladder.
Any fibroblast that is part of a spleen.
Any endothelial cell that is part of a spleen.
A large, granular, liver specific natural killer cell that adheres to the endothelial cells of the hepatic sinusoid.

definition.value: Pit cells are named for the presence of large cytoplasmic granules that resemble pits (pips) of fruit.

value.value: Any mesenchymal stem cell that is part of a placenta.
Any capillary endothelial cell that is part of a placenta.
Any fibroblast that is part of a cardiac ventricle.
Any fibroblast that is part of a cardiac atrium.
